com.b2international.snowowl.snomed.core.domain

Class SnomedConcept

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.b2international.snowowl.core.domain.BaseComponent

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IComponent, DefinitionStatusProvider, java.io.Serializable

    public final class SnomedConcept
extends SnomedCoreComponent
implements DefinitionStatusProvider
    Represents a SNOMED CT concept.
    Concepts returned by search requests are populated based on the expand parameters passed into the ResourceRequestBuilder.setExpand(String) methods. The expand parameters can be nested allowing a fine control for the details returned in the resultset. The supported expand parameters are:

    • pt() - returns the Preferred Term for the
      • locale set by ResourceRequestBuilder.setLocales(java.util.List) method.
    • fsn() - returns the Fully Specified Name (fsn) for the
      • locale set by ResourceRequestBuilder.setLocales(java.util.List) method.
    • descriptions() - returns the descriptions of the concept
    • relationships() - returns the relationships of the concept
    • descendants(direct:true|false) - returns the all or the only the direct descendants of the concept based on the inferred tree.
    • ancestors(direct:true|false) - returns the all or the only the direct ancestors of the concept based on the inferred tree.
    • statedDescendants(direct:true|false) - returns the all or the only the direct descendants of the concept based on the stated tree.
    • statedAncestors(direct:true|false) - returns the all or the only the direct ancestors of the concept based on the stated tree.
    • members() - returns the reference set members referencing this component
    • preferredDescriptions() - expands the preferred descriptions for each matching concept
    The number of expanded fields can be controlled with the limit: directive.
    For example: ancestors(direct:false, limit:1000)

    Expand parameters can be nested to further expand or filter the details returned. For example the expand string:

    descriptions(expand(type:"typeId"))

    returns only the descriptions with the specified typeId

    See Also:
    BaseResourceRequestBuilder#setLocales(java.util.List), SnomedDescription, SnomedRelationship, SnomedReferenceSet, SnomedReferenceSetMember, Serialized Form
